OL,3,CIndia rejects UK parliament report on
OL,4,Ctransnational repression
OL,6,FWhile the report reserves its sharpest
OL,7,Fcriticism for what it terms the "three
OL,8,Fmost flagrant perpetrators" ` China,
OL,9,FRussia, and Iran ` India's inclusion,
OL,10,Fparticularly the accusation of abusing
OL,11,FINTERPOL's Red Notice mechanism for
OL,12,Fpolitical ends, has sparked sharp
OL,13,Fpushback from New Delhi.
OL,15,FThe committee's findings draw heavily
OL,16,Ffrom evidence submitted by UK-based
OL,17,FSikh advocacy groups, including the
OL,18,FSikh Federation (UK) and Sikhs for
OL,19,FJustice.
